text: [Music]
hello I'm Bonita a customer service
specialist here at the AWS office in
Cape Town today I'm going to show you
how to view your software products that
you've subscribed to through the AWS
Marketplace let's get
started to view your active AWS
Marketplace subscriptions first sign
into the AWS Management
console next navigate to the AWS
Marketplace console from the left
navigation pane choose manage
subscriptions a list appears that shows
you all the software subscriptions that
you currently have through the AWS
Marketplace you can see details such as
the product name the subscription start
date the charge period and more to view
additional details about a specific
subscription choose subscription from
the list
the subscription detail page appears
where you can see information such as
usage metrics billing details and
subscription
modifications so now you know how to
view the software products that you've
subscribed to through the AWS
Marketplace thanks for watching and
happy cloud computing from all of us
here at AWS
[Music]
